{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CbeHUEH7iQ69mQAqCi8knX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the setup. There are two Ingress resources:\n1. `rate-api` - routes /api to rate-echo service - no rate limiting\n2. `rate-health` - routes /health to rate-echo service - should remain unlimited\n\nI need to add rate limiting annotations to the `rate-api` ingress. For ingress-nginx, the annotations for rate limiting are:\n- `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-rps: \"1\"` - limit to 1 request per second\n- `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-connections: \"1\"` - limit connections (optional)\n- `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-req-status-code: \"429\"` - return 429 instead of the default 503 when the rate limit is exceeded\n\nI'll add these annotations to the rate-api ingress to enforce the rate limiting.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":498,"cache_read_input_tokens":31428,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":498},"output_tokens":12,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9526465e-ea0d-4ba6-aa1f-f0ed131e421a","uuid":"f69eba6c-bb06-4b13-9b34-d0f4288c8cfc","request_id":"req_011CcQ16qwWJGf9dR9kNScDP"}
